item.title: Landing At Moorabbin
item.description: You should rely on your flight intructor, not the personal notes of some guy on the internet, for navigating the Moorabbin airspace. Before the VFR Finding GMH Finding Carrum From the training area, fly along coast. Carrum is at major outlet/inlet from the bay. Proceedure Decend to 1500 Trim aircraft to reduce workload Listen to ATIS on 120.9 Transponder to 3000 Tune to 118.1 for GMH, 123.0 for Carrum Radio Call Moorabbin Tower Cessna 172 Tango Foxtrot Bravo Overhead GMH/Carrum at 1500 With Information Qubec Inbound GHM Overfly Tango Foxtrot Bravo Maintain 1500 Overfly Field Contact 123.
